column2: i1evrc:",,,,,,Iteration 1.5,,,,,,,,,,07/Sep/21 4:00 AM,,,,,,,,,,,,"{""issueId"":323395,""testStatuses"":[]}",,,,,,,,,,"17/Sep/21 4:41 PM;Ben.Taylor@rtx.com;Derek Peterson provided the following Standard and Optional requirements.  The optional items in *bold* type were implemented in the seven Equinix Performance Hubs.

column1: *Standard:*
* 4 Sided Cage (no roof/top)
* Cage Hole Diameter - 2.5”x1.5” +or less+
* Cage Material – 1.5mm thick +or more+, polyester powder coated in Pale Grey steel (aluminum was used for Equinox)
* Cage Gap – Bottom of cage to floor 6” +or less+
* Badge Reader on Door
* Raised or Slab floor based on IX location
* M6 Machine Screws, M6 Nylock Nuts
*Optional Add-ons:*
* 5 Sided Cage (Top/Roof) *(added for Performance Hubs)*
* Additional Mesh around sides and floor (to reduce hole diameter, secure floor)
* Biometric Reader on Door (Standard are most but add on at others)
* Kickplate around cage to reduce cage to floor size *(added for Performance Hubs)*
* Camera/Video (Standard at most but add on at others) *(Axis camera added for Performance Hubs)*

Anne Anderson (Compliance Architecture) and Mike Bryant (Connected Infrastructure Engineering) sent the below Technical Requirements (in the identical format).  Anne’s and Mike’s information aligns with Derek’s.  The ES and BU Global Security teams are referenced as the source of the “Technical Requirements” section.
# Technical Requirements _(implemented for Equinix Performance Hubs)_
# Cage Construction:
# Cages must be 5 sided comprised of 4 walls and a cage roof.
# Cage must be extended from the floor to a minimum height of 2.4 meters (8ft)
* Cage Hole diameter must be 2.5”x1.5” or less
# Cage material must be at least 1.5mm thick steel
# Steel kickplate or trim must be added to eliminate gap between bottom of cage and floor
Scott Paradis confirmed the above requirements and identified the following additional items:
* The cage must extend below raised floors – (Equinix stated the floor is slab concrete in the 9/7/2021 meeting)
* The cage must extend above drop ceilings (or be roofed as stated above)
* Technical Requirements apply to shared areas
* If RTX owns the whole area, the existing walls are acceptable
*Additional Items Discussed:*
* There is no plan on using Equinix Smart Hands

* Kyndryl is planning on using onsite physical support with US persons on the ground (onboarded through RTX);;;","17/Sep/21 4:46 PM;Ben.Taylor@rtx.com;Follow-up email sent T*o:* Doyle, Dan P RTX <[dan.doyle@rtx.com

NET - 001 - Risk to network availability for few sites during Chicago Transition,NOPT-4748,322912,,Risk,Resolved,NOPT,NTD - Optimus,software,erika.childree@raytheon.com,,,Low,Done,Arun.Limaye@rtx.com,Arun.Limaye@rtx.com,Arun.Limaye@rtx.com,16/Sep/21 12:58 PM,27/Jan/22 10:58 PM,22/Feb/22 2:44 PM,27/Jan/22 10:58 PM,,,0,001,Network,Optimus,,,,,,,"1/18  - It is not clear if Chicago VPN solution will failover (Last update is - VPN Solution doesn't have an option to pick CH or DAL, it just load balances)
2021 - update
Recent troubleshooting has identified that Tech Failover from Chicago to Dallas is not working as expected.
There is a GPS to BAE divestiture coming up that is dependent on Chicago being up.
This has resulted in dry run next week being cancelled and having to come up with new dates for those activities
Identifying new dates on the calendar is challenging as all weeks are ""booked"" - so there is a possibility that Chicago transition will get delayed by multiple weeks

column2: i1erkr:",,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,01/Dec/21 5:00 AM,,,,,,,,,,,,"{""issueId"":322687,""testStatuses"":[]}",,,,,,,,,,"17/Nov/21 5:21 PM;Kristi.Craig.Moses@raytheon.com;11.17.21:  The code, to do the authentication, has been implemented and work is currently underway to implement a feature flag for this capability so that we are able to toggle it off/on.  Our main developer SMEs (Arash, Natt, Simon) are currently without RTX accounts so will be locked out of doing certain things once the Authentication is turned on.  While the code, to add the feature flag, is being worked we are working in parallel to get RTX laptop requests pushed through the queue so that they will still be able to perform the necessary duties once the authentication is turned on.  Right now I don't have an updated End Date, for this feature.  I will know more once we are able to get the requests submitted. ;;;","01/Dec/21 2:51 PM;Kristi.Craig.Moses@raytheon.com;no updates to report; this feature is still not currently being worked but is still on track for Iteration 3.6;;;","08/Dec/21 3:09 PM;Kristi.Craig.Moses@raytheon.com;no updates to report; this feature is still not currently being worked but is still on track for Iteration 3.6;;;","16/Dec/21 7:59 AM;Kristi.Craig.Moses@raytheon.com;Work on this feature has not started but there is nothing, right now, which makes me think we are not on track to have it done by the end of Iteration 3.6;;;","05/Jan/22 3:59 PM;Kristi.Craig.Moses@raytheon.com;Nothing new to report just yet;;;","14/Jan/22 11:44 AM;Kristi.Craig.Moses@raytheon.com;nothing new to report;;;","24/Jan/22 7:58 AM;Kristi.Craig.Moses@raytheon.com;This is one of the components that will be impacted by the approval of DoZen.   We will work towards targeted deployment once we have a handle on what we will have to do to get this to work inside of DoZen.;;;","27/Jan/22 12:39 PM;Elizabeth_A_Penisten@raytheon.com; Cleanup in preparation for next PI;;;",,,,

column2: i1erjf:",,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,20/Oct/21 4:00 AM,,,,,,,,,,,,"{""issueId"":322681,""testStatuses"":[]}",,,,,,,,,,"17/Nov/21 5:17 PM;Kristi.Craig.Moses@raytheon.com;Currently in work for Iteration 3.2 which started today (11.17.21);;;","01/Dec/21 2:50 PM;Kristi.Craig.Moses@raytheon.com;On target to complete implementation of this feature by the end of Iteration 3.3 which started today (12.01.21);;;","08/Dec/21 3:08 PM;Kristi.Craig.Moses@raytheon.com;nothing new to report;;;","16/Dec/21 7:56 AM;Kristi.Craig.Moses@raytheon.com;This feature is currently in work and seems to be on target to complete in January.;;;","05/Jan/22 3:41 PM;Kristi.Craig.Moses@raytheon.com;nothing new to report just yet.;;;","14/Jan/22 10:31 AM;Kristi.Craig.Moses@raytheon.com;This week the decision was made to place this work on hold due to the outstanding DoZen decision.  The expectation is that if DoZen is brought on board the Local Navigation/Breadcrumbs will be something that is available in the ""out of the box"" solution.;;;","24/Jan/22 7:57 AM;Kristi.Craig.Moses@raytheon.com;Implementation of this feature was completed, in PI 3, however it is one of the components that will be impacted by the approval of DoZen.   We will work towards targeted deployment once we have a handle on what we will have to do to get this to work inside of DoZen.;;;","27/Jan/22 12:39 PM;Elizabeth_A_Penisten@raytheon.com; Cleanup in preparation for next PI;;;",,,,

column2: i1erj7:",,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,01/Oct/21 4:00 AM,,,,,,,,,,,,"{""issueId"":322680,""testStatuses"":[]}",,,,,,,,,,"17/Nov/21 5:15 PM;Kristi.Craig.Moses@raytheon.com;From what I've been able to gather this feature has been deployed to Production but not turned on.  I will follow up with our development team, in the morning (11.18.21) and will provide a better update tomorrow.;;;","01/Dec/21 2:43 PM;Kristi.Craig.Moses@raytheon.com;The search ""type ahead"" feature is currently being indirectly blocked by the fact that the implementation of the ""authentication"" feature is still in work.  We are on target to finish implementation by the end of Iteration 3.3 at which point we should be able to target ""releasing"" authentication along with this search soon after.  I'm not sure about the history that went into the decision to link the 2 features since you don't have to be authenticated in order to search; however I'm working to find out the effort to decouple them in the event that releasing the Authentication flows too far beyond the end of Iteration 3.3.;;;","16/Dec/21 7:53 AM;Kristi.Craig.Moses@raytheon.com;We will release this when we release the Authentication feature which, right now, I believe we can target for early 2022.  ;;;","05/Jan/22 3:39 PM;Kristi.Craig.Moses@raytheon.com;nothing new to report just yet;;;","14/Jan/22 9:51 AM;Kristi.Craig.Moses@raytheon.com;The current implementation of the type ahead feature has the feature linked with the profile feature.  We have created stories to decouple the 2 so that we can deploy them independent of each other.  We are targeting having the updates made, tested and deployed by the end of the month.;;;","27/Jan/22 12:39 PM;Elizabeth_A_Penisten@raytheon.com; Cleanup in preparation for next PI;;;",,,,,,

column2: i1eo5n:",,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,"{""issueId"":322100,""testStatuses"":[]}",,,,,,Yes,,,,"15/Sep/21 9:25 AM;juan.ramirez2@rtx.com;9/15: Strategic Partnerships has sent the BOM for quoting, quote expected by 09/21;;;","22/Sep/21 4:38 PM;juan.ramirez2@rtx.com;09/22: A quote will not be provided until determination made of local currency, tax review, and what is local contract entity.  Escalated to Legal.;;;","23/Sep/21 8:44 AM;juan.ramirez2@rtx.com;09/23: Evan working with Linda Kent to determine legal entities for quotes.;;;","27/Sep/21 2:25 PM;juan.ramirez2@rtx.com;09/27: Legal Entities for Singapore, London, and Frankfurt have been provided to Equinix and WWT for BOM and Cage quotes; International BOM has been provided to WWT for quoting.

column1: The Scope of International hubs has been limited to London, Frankfurt, and Singapore for 2022.

;;;","30/Sep/21 4:56 PM;juan.ramirez2@rtx.com;09/30: Targeting to submit to Strategic Parnerships by 10/08.;;;","11/Oct/21 4:36 PM;juan.ramirez2@rtx.com;10/11: Waiting on quote from WWT to include Cisco and Dell devices.  Evan working with Dan for an update.  Quotes requested per country in local currency. Pending in-country maintenance quotes from Cisco.;;;","14/Oct/21 3:35 PM;juan.ramirez2@rtx.com;10/14: International BOM continues to be quoted.;;;","18/Oct/21 3:45 PM;juan.ramirez2@rtx.com;10/18: International BOM continues to be quoted, added as a risk to the project.  Strategic Partnerships working this item; target date of October 1st has been missed.  Right now we are targeting April 18, 2022, Q1 is no longer on the table.  We will continue to communicate as we get order lead times, we have no way to mitigate.  This also impacts Data Center's schedule.;;;","01/Nov/21 4:39 PM;juan.ramirez2@rtx.com;11/01: Dan Doyle has returned from OOO and continues working with International Finance teams to move BOM along.  ;;;","03/Nov/21 4:55 PM;juan.ramirez2@rtx.com;11/03: Finalizing equipment quote to submit to Strategic Partnerships to create PO orders; targeting 11/05.;;;","30/Nov/21 9:18 AM;juan.ramirez2@rtx.com;11/30: Final quotes completed on 11/19, waiting for contracts to be finalized with Strategic Partnerships.;;;","14/Dec/21 8:43 AM;jamie.harris2@rtx.com;12/14: Met with finance on a path forward, working to add Collins to FPNA system; working on PO getting sent to WWT;;;"

RTXConnect: Left Panel User Created Favorites,NOPT-4662,321859,,Feature,Cancelled,NOPT,NTD - Optimus,software,erika.childree@raytheon.com,,,Medium,Cancelled,Elizabeth_A_Penisten@raytheon.com,Fairy.Bagga@rtx.com,Fairy.Bagga@rtx.com,14/Sep/21 3:26 PM,27/Jan/22 12:39 PM,22/Feb/22 2:44 PM,27/Jan/22 12:39 PM,,,0,Applications,RTXConnect,,,,,,,,"The scope of this feature is to make sure that the hRTN end user created favorites are imported into RTXConnect, and end users from all BUs can create personal favorites.
- There will be company created resources (the current resource links). These can be favorited and added to the my favorites section
- End users can create their own friendly links and favorites in the folder section
* https://www.figma.com/file/enlFmkGWzkaUwKjuRDG3Rw/53387---Left-Panel-%7C-Favorites-Final-Designs?node-id=1%3A171
Benefit Hypothesis:

Enables end users to easily access quick links that they need",,christopher.stournaras@rtx.com,Elizabeth_A_Penisten@raytheon.com,Fairy.Bagga@rtx.com,Kristi.Craig.Moses@raytheon.com,,,,,,,,,,NOPT-5106,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,NOPT-458,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,Applications,15/Nov/21 5:00 AM,,,,,,,,,,,,85%,,,,,,,,,,,,,18/Feb/22 5:00 AM,,,ghx-label-3,,,,,,,Left Panel User Created Favorites,To Do,,,,,,,,,,,,,[],,,,,,,,,"0
column2: i1emtv:",,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,01/Oct/21 4:00 AM,,,,,,,,,,,,"{""issueId"":321859,""testStatuses"":[]}",,,,,,,,,,"05/Oct/21 12:52 PM;christopher.stournaras@rtx.com;- Can we import all the current links currated by RIS and RMD businesses to sitecore, this is in XML file. ;;;","17/Nov/21 5:09 PM;Kristi.Craig.Moses@raytheon.com;Notes 11.17.21:  this feature is still currently blocked by the fact that the authentication has not been deployed yet for RTXConnect.  The code, to do the authentication, has been implemented and work is currently underway to implement a feature flag for this capability so that we are able to toggle it off/on.  Our main developer SMEs (Arash, Natt, Simon) are currently without RTX accounts so will be locked out of doing certain things once the Authentication is turned on.  While the code, to add the feature flag, is being worked we are working in parallel to get RTX laptop requests pushed through the queue so that they will still be able to perform the necessary duties once the authentication is turned on.  Right now I don't have an updated End Date, for this feature.  I will know more once we are able to get the requests submitted.  Additionally, the team is still working to flush out the user stories for migrating the existing oneRTN content into RTXConnect.

column1: Once the authentication is in place we will be able to move forward with the implementation of this feature.  I hope to be able to provide a more firm date after the Thanksgiving break.;;;","01/Dec/21 2:32 PM;Kristi.Craig.Moses@raytheon.com;There are about 5 more stories (out of 14) to implement, within this feature, but we will not be able to ""release"" it to Production until the Authentication is completed so that the tool will know what ""favorites"" to load for a logged in user or which user profile to update based on new ""favorites"" added by the user.  We are on target to complete authentication by the end of iteration 3.3.;;;","08/Dec/21 3:07 PM;Kristi.Craig.Moses@raytheon.com;On track to complete implementation of remaining stories by end of Iteration 3.3;;;","16/Dec/21 7:49 AM;Kristi.Craig.Moses@raytheon.com;We still have 3 more stories/bugs to implement.  Arash was working this feature and is out for the rest of 2021.  We will finish this out when we come back in January;;;","05/Jan/22 2:55 PM;Kristi.Craig.Moses@raytheon.com;Arash just returned, from break, today so there is nothing new to report on this feature just yet;;;","14/Jan/22 8:58 AM;Kristi.Craig.Moses@raytheon.com;We have all but 1 one the stories (and 1 bug), in this feature, implemented so are very close to having this done.  Barring any new bugs cropping up I'm pushing to see if we can the last story implemented and the bug validated by the end of next week (01.21.22).  ;;;","24/Jan/22 7:52 AM;Kristi.Craig.Moses@raytheon.com;We still one User Story that is being worked in this feature.  The deployment of this feature is dependent upon Authentication which is currently on hold while we await official approval of DoZen.  We will target deployment (as part of PI 4) once we have a handle on how the Authentication will work with DoZen brought on board. ;;;","27/Jan/22 12:39 PM;Elizabeth_A_Penisten@raytheon.com; Cleanup in preparation for next PI;;;",,,

168 domains;;;","02/Feb/22 9:55 AM;Ben.Taylor@rtx.com;12/2/2021.  Kyndryl to procure PCAP, Identity Management and Load Balancers under Amendment 49 of their agreement with RTX.
As of 2/2/2022, the identity management equipment is not scheduled for delivery until 5/6/2022.  Kyndryl is working to pull delivery into April.
During PI Planning on 12/1, Eric Schmidt stated the ID Kit in side the performance hubs (PH) could support 25% of the application capacity if the WAN connection to the PH has capacity.
The ID Kit at the East Colo is not required for the 5/1 DC MVP, but the ID Kit is required to prior to the full workload migrations.
ADX and Network teams need to collaborate on the planning and implementation.;;;",,,,

Response time between AWSGov and AzureCommercial exceeds thresholds for development,NOPT-4649,320968,,Risk,Resolved,NOPT,NTD - Optimus,software,erika.childree@raytheon.com,,,High,Done,Camille.Fremed2@rtx.com,Camille.Fremed2@rtx.com,Camille.Fremed2@rtx.com,10/Sep/21 2:17 PM,15/Nov/21 11:04 AM,22/Feb/22 2:44 PM,15/Nov/21 11:04 AM,,,0,Dependency,team#CYB,,,,,,,,"The current response time from Azure Commercial, where the EIM In-House second Dev environment resides, to the database that resides in AWSGov ranges from 35 to 60 ms.  This exceeds the recommended threshold for response times between the db and the IIQ servers.  We have NO fallback plan as the alternatives are non-starters.  Alternatives are:
1.  Provision resources in AWS commercial - have requested, and were informed this is not feasible.

2.  Create another dev database in Azure Commercial - would be non-standard, Oracle license required, and unsupported.",,Camille.Fremed2@rtx.com,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,NOPT-4648,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,Cybersecurity,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,Medium,Schedule,,,,,,,,,,[],,,,,,,Highly Likely - 75%,,"0

Non-US persons cannot work in AWSGov (Console access)
AWS Commercial is non-viable until the new RTX AWS environment is provisioned

column1: NET - 009 - NOC Monitoring, Day 1 (Performance Hub + Remote Site WAN transition),NOPT-4622,320100,,Feature,Done,NOPT,NTD - Optimus,software,erika.childree@raytheon.com,,,Medium,Done,max.chang@rtx.com,max.chang@rtx.com,max.chang@rtx.com,08/Sep/21 10:21 AM,08/Feb/22 12:47 PM,22/Feb/22 2:44 PM,14/Dec/21 1:42 PM,,,0,Network,Network_Operations,Optimus,Transition,WAN/MAN,,,,,"This feature includes stories in the NET - 009 - Infra Ops Design workstream related to NOC monitoring and tools expected for Day 1 to support both the augmented Equinix Performance Hubs and Remote Site WAN.

Day 1 NOC monitoring support includes Network Fault Monitoring for the Equinix WAN components in the 6 CONUS hubs, the integrated heritage Rockwell Collins remote site WAN routers at 65 sites, in addition to the existing UTC Corp, GRC, PWA, PWC devices supported by the Global RTX NOC/NMC today. RIS & RMD WAN/MAN remains out of scope for Day 1 and monitoring support for these devices will be accomplished in the current-state tool.
+These Network Tools will be used to support Day 1:+
* *Network Device Availability Monitoring (NOC/NMC Tools):*
Broadcom Spectrum, Statseeker
* *Network Performance Monitoring (NetOps Toolsets):*
Netscout nG1 NPM, Netscout nGPulse Synthetics
* *Network Configuration Change Management (NOC/NetOps Tools):*

VMWare Smart Assurance",,kjetil.storaker@rtx.com,max.chang@rtx.com,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,NOPT-4780,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,NOPT-2236,NOPT-2237,NOPT-3387,NOPT-3398,NOPT-3747,NOPT-3191,NOPT-3195,NOPT-3735,NOPT-3196,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,Network,28/Feb/22 5:00 AM,08/Sep/21 4:00 AM,,,,NOC Monitoring,,,,55.0,,,70%,,,,,,,,,,,,,01/Mar/22 4:59 AM,,,ghx-label-9,002,009,Network,Network_Operations,WAN/MAN,,"NET - 002 - NOC Monitoring, Day 1 (Performance Hub + Remote Site WAN transition)",To Do,,,,,,,,,,,,,[],,,,,,,,,"0

column1: NET - 001 - Schedule Risk to uplifts for 4/6 completing in 2021 (Dallas, Chicago, Los Angeles, Seattle),NOPT-4620,319515,,Risk,Resolved,NOPT,NTD - Optimus,software,erika.childree@raytheon.com,,,Highest,Done,Arun.Limaye@rtx.com,Arun.Limaye@rtx.com,Arun.Limaye@rtx.com,03/Sep/21 4:29 PM,27/Jan/22 11:29 AM,22/Feb/22 2:44 PM,21/Dec/21 9:47 AM,,,0,001,Network,Optimus,Program_Risk,,,,,,"As of 11/1 - There are 3 transitions / 5 uplifts to go from here till end of the year - total of 8 hub events remaining
As team was working to schedule these 8 hub events they have to work with following schedule constraints
* Change Freeze
* Dry Run required before every transition in a +prior week and close to the week+ of transition
* Space out hub events +across weeks+ for Dry run / Transition and Uplift
* Equinix completes new cage construction for each hub for transition and uplift
* Upcoming PTO for often tapped resources
With the above four constraints it is proving difficult to schedule ALL 8 hub events in 2021
* Schedule can accommodate in 2021 - 2 Events - Ashburn Uplift and one more event * (will have to choose one event from list below potentially Dallas Uplift IF WWT is able to deliver)
* Schedule cannot  accommodate in 2021 - 6 Events - which is Uplifts for Chicago/Dallas/Los Angeles/Seattle AND Transitions for Chicago/LA/Seattle

One mitigation strategy is to combine Transition and Uplift as a single event - however earliest this mitigation can be implemented is January after atleast one more uplift is performed",,Arun.Limaye@rtx.com,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,NOPT-8866,,,NOPT-3727,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,Network,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,10/Aug/21 3:59 AM,,,,,,,,,NOPT-652,,,,High,Schedule,,,,,,,,,,[],,,,,,,Likely - 50%,,"0

column1: However it does look like while we will able to get all transitions done / get primary uplifts and installs done (Miami/Ashburn/Boston), we are at risk for completing uplift for remaining 4 hubs.
Projection is by end of year 2021
* 3 primary hubs will be fully transitioned and uplifted
** Uplifted = new equipment integrated and configured
* 4 secondary hubs will be fully transitioned and not uplifted

** projection new equipment will be +available+ at the new cages to be integrated/configured eventually;;;","20/Sep/21 12:52 AM;Arun.Limaye@rtx.com;Chicago uplift has been accommodated by optimizing space out of dry runs/transitions;;;","27/Sep/21 2:48 PM;Arun.Limaye@rtx.com;During PI pre-planning discussion - there was a request made to adjust Dallas v/s Chicago uplift priority. Work in progress on that front.;;;","11/Nov/21 1:13 PM;Arun.Limaye@rtx.com;This has been accepted - PCR has been raised for moving Dallas uplift to next year.;;;","21/Dec/21 9:47 AM;Arun.Limaye@rtx.com;PCR accepted;;;",,,,,,,

column1: NET-002: Performance Hub Hosted Resources (IDM Kits, Mail Gateway, etc.),NOPT-4611,318796,,Feature,To Do,NOPT,NTD - Optimus,software,erika.childree@raytheon.com,,,Medium,,richard.p.hill@rtx.com,Sahin.Thajudeen@rtx.com,Keith.Melanson@rtx.com,02/Sep/21 12:27 PM,14/Dec/21 8:10 PM,22/Feb/22 2:44 PM,,,,0,002,Network,Optimus,,,,,,,"Per Troy Abraham: Fortinet firewalls are being deployed ONLY as a temporary solution for route symmetry.  There is still no architecture completed. We are responding to the WAN request to deploy the systems only.

I and Meghan will be the leads for the firewall configurations. We are sending 6 Fortinet firewalls with basic mgmt configs to WWT and they will deploy the devices in the performance hubs. The infrastructure team will be responsible for the overall project and for architecture. I will ensure those on the firewall teams who do not have Fortinet experience will get training.
Make resources network accessible:
* Mail Gateway - Chad Lang
* IDM Kits - Eric Schmidt
* Identity Kit Firewall - Troy Abraham
* Zscaler (Internet Proxy) - Chad Lang

column2: i1e0v7:",,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,31/Aug/21 4:00 AM,,,,,,,,,,,,"{""issueId"":318008,""testStatuses"":[]}",,,,,,,,,,"31/Aug/21 10:42 AM;damalia.thomas@rtx.com;Private Cloud design is dependent on the Cyber firewall vendor. There are three vendors approved by VMware for the Private Cloud; Fortinet, Palo Alto  and Check Point which is supported by three vendors. Once the vendor is selected the PC team will need to update the LLD which will take about 60 days to complete. This design  is required to build out the PC.;;;","31/Aug/21 10:44 AM;damalia.thomas@rtx.com;Based on internal meeting with David, Marty and John Conners the Cyber team has decided to stick with its exsisting infrastructure and go with Check Point. I have reached out to the team to confirm if there are any risks with the selection of this vendor. PC team has confirmed there is no risk with go with this vendor.  Marty to provide clarificaito on Datacenter risk;;;","17/Sep/21 11:08 PM;damalia.thomas@rtx.com;

column1: * We need to order 3 x Pair of FW’s for the 3 greenfield dc build ( East, PDC1 and West Colo locations)
* Timeline for delivery and build Q4 2021 – West colo may be later
* A competitive bid from Checkpoint and Palo Alto and not an RFP – the requirement is small
* There will be a bigger opportunity for Palo later on and this should be seen as their opportunity to prove their value / ability to meet our requirements
* Goal would be to order next week
* Funded from Optimus DC budget.

;;;","21/Sep/21 11:03 AM;damalia.thomas@rtx.com;Goal is to recevie competitive bid from vendors and place the firewall order this week;;;","26/Oct/21 3:07 PM;damalia.thomas@rtx.com;NextGen Firewall orders have been placed. column1: Lack of Visibility to App RFP Process/Timeline for AMS Partner,NOPT-4507,316795,,Story,Done,NOPT,NTD - Optimus,software,erika.childree@raytheon.com,,,Medium,Resolved,,Ashley.Kindsvatter@rtx.com,Ashley.Kindsvatter@rtx.com,25/Aug/21 2:25 PM,14/Dec/21 8:09 PM,22/Feb/22 2:44 PM,22/Sep/21 9:05 AM,,,0,DC_App_Migration,OSOS,Punchlist,,,,,,,"* Assumptions
** Due to the lack of visibility to timeline/scope, apps scrum team is unable to understand impact to Data Center timeline/dependencies
* Key questions:
** What is the expected date for AMS selection?
** When are app factories expected to be staffed and onboarded (internal and AMS)?
** What is the timeline for the app rationalization and migration readiness work?
* Work being blocked or risks:

** Unable to understand impact to data center overall timeline (migration and exits)",,Ashley.Kindsvatter@rtx.com,howard.miles2@rtx.com,juan.ramirez2@rtx.com,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,Datacenter,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,NOPT-4570,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,[],,,,,,,,,"0
column2: i1dv6j:",,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,"{""issueId"":316795,""testStatuses"":[]}",,,,,,,,,,"30/Aug/21 7:21 PM;Ashley.Kindsvatter@rtx.com;I had an introduction call today with Jaime Gamez (PO of Apps AMS scrum team).  They are beginning refinement sessions this week for PI2 and will add me and Steven Pankretic to those meetings.;;;","31/Aug/21 9:08 AM;howard.miles2@rtx.com;DC teams will be added to the Apps & AMS scrum meetings, first meeting is 9/1. Confirm on Thursday ;;;","08/Sep/21 9:14 AM;howard.miles2@rtx.com;Apps team has pushed the refinement meetings, no updated date provided.;;;","22/Sep/21 9:04 AM;juan.ramirez2@rtx.com;09/22: Ashley met with team and now has visibility to timeline; item can be closed. ;;;",,,,,,,,

column2: i1dtqz:",,,,,,Iteration 1.5,PI 2021 Iteration 2.1,,,,,,,,,23/Sep/21 4:00 AM,,,,,,,,,,,,"{""issueId"":316549,""testStatuses"":[]}",,,,,,,,,,"01/Sep/21 12:01 AM;Arun.Limaye@rtx.com;Arun 8/31 - There are three different Change Approval Boards (CAB)s possible for an RTX change - Heritage Raytheon /  Heritage UTC / Rockwell Collins.  For putting uplift in production one may have to get approval from ALL three CABs making this process cumbersome. Bryan De Souza is aware and is following up on it.;;;","02/Sep/21 9:07 AM;howard.miles2@rtx.com;Per Arun pending direction from Marty and Evan on which CAB process(s) to use;;;","08/Sep/21 9:12 AM;howard.miles2@rtx.com;Pending response from Adam Parker to provide clarification and direction on the correct RTX CAB Process. Updated Sprint to PI 2.3;;;","22/Nov/21 4:49 PM;Ben.Taylor@rtx.com;WWT/Kyndryl tech sync sessions continue each Monday.  Kyndryl shared sizing data and WWT updated design to accommodate new data.  11/22 - Kyndryl is developing hardware BOM for RU based design session.

* Data Access and Segmentation
* PowerStore Block Storage

* Data Protection Suite

column2: i1drjn:",,,,,,PI 2021 Iteration 2.5,,,,,,,,,,22/Nov/21 5:00 AM,,,,,,,,,,,,"{""issueId"":316252,""testStatuses"":[]}",,,,,,,,,,"04/Nov/21 10:51 AM;Ben.Taylor@rtx.com;Technical Design Team is hosting transition workshops with the Kyndryl and RTX teams during the weeks of 11/1 and 11/8.  The detail designs for DC Network Fabric, Compute and Storage are shared with the teams.

column1: NOPT-4445 covers the Technical Design Team work to provide design support to RTX and Kyndryl for smooth transition to the build phase.;;;","07/Dec/21 9:41 PM;Ben.Taylor@rtx.com;WWT to provide design support to Kyndryl.  Multiple tech sync sessions with Kyndryl to review design.  Also hosting multiple sessions with RTX to review design.

Support work will continue through Feb 2022.;;;","09/Dec/21 3:00 PM;Ben.Taylor@rtx.com;WWT will continue to provide support for the design, but there is no specific deliverables going forward.  This Story is complete.

WWT has been hosting technical sync sessions with Kyndryl and leading the LLD review sessions with RTX and Kyndryl.  The ARB LLD is approved and the detail LLD docs are foundationally complete - meaning implementation details like share names have not been determined.

Kyndryl Storage Engineering owns this level of the detail.  They will be managing the system, and they must understand how that naming aligns to the data - in order to assure that it is managed properly.;;;",,,,,,,,,

column2: i1drir:",,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,16/Sep/21 4:00 AM,,,,,,,,,,,,"{""issueId"":316248,""testStatuses"":[]}",,,,,,,,,,"05/Oct/21 2:10 PM;Ben.Taylor@rtx.com;Started transition sessions with Kyndryl on 9/16.  Sessions included review of approved ARB document and detail LLD Recommendations for storage, compute and DR.

column1: Also started Operations Gap Analysis to enable smooth transition.
Updated Start Date to reflect work start date.;;;","15/Oct/21 2:07 PM;Ben.Taylor@rtx.com;Tech Sync sessions between WWT and Kyndryl continue on weekly cadence.

Kyndryl introduced an alternative IBM backup solution.  A special 5ITB session on 10/7 reviewed the Dell Suite and the IBM suite.  The Technical Design Team will move forward with the existing Dell suite.
Kyndryl introduced Rubrik for backup solution.  Rubrik is used by at least one RTX BU.  RTX needs to decide if Rubrik and Dell will be used going forward or select one solution.

;;;","27/Oct/21 11:23 AM;Ben.Taylor@rtx.com;Tech Sync sessions between WWT and Kyndryl continue on weekly cadence.;;;","04/Nov/21 10:16 AM;Ben.Taylor@rtx.com;Tech sync sessions continue between WWT and Kyndryl.  Starting week of 11/1, the detail designs for DC Network Fabric, OpenGear, Compute, Storage (Block/File/Object), Dell Data Protection Suite and VxRail are shared with the entire team including RTX and Kyndryl.

The design transition sessions will continue through 11/19 with ongoing design support continuing through Dec 2021. ;;;","22/Nov/21 4:51 PM;Ben.Taylor@rtx.com;WWT/Kyndryl tech sync sessions continue each Monday.  Kyndryl shared sizing data and WWT updated design to accommodate new data.  11/22 - Kyndryl is developing hardware BOM for RU based design session.
The new findings are shared with RTX at 2P Eastern.  The meeting topics include the following:
* DC Network Fabric
* Data Access and Segmentation
* PowerStore Block Storage
* PowerScale
* Data Protection Suite

The entire team met multiple times per topic and the LLD Design documents were updated for final approval.  Design approval expected by 12/3.  Once approved, the LLD design transitions to supporting the Kyndryl build process.

Updated Sprint to PI 2.4.;;;","16/Dec/21 8:58 PM;Ben.Taylor@rtx.com;The Kyndryl KT sessions to review the LLD documents, answer questions and update the documents based on feedback wrapped on 12/16/2021.  The attached meeting minutes reflect the discussions and the alignment that KT sessions are complete.

column1: During weeks of 9/13 and 9/20, new requirements were uncovered around the block and file storage requirements across the various BUs.  Also, the Hardware BOM for the entire Data Center architecture elevated in priority and requires additional meeting of the Design Team.  The Design team’s priority is on providing a more detailed hardware list for the Hardware BOM order that Marty has requested.
* The hardware list effort requires more detail than originally expected

* The team is supporting Kyndryl transition to a greater detail than planned;;;","05/Oct/21 1:22 PM;Ben.Taylor@rtx.com;The risk for extending the date is resolved and deliverable will complete on schedule.

This is issue is complete and the LLD will be part of the EDTAC / ARB review on 10/28/2021.;;;",,,,,,,,,

(E) AMS and Factory Team Formation,NOPT-4435,316037,,Feature,Done,NOPT,NTD - Optimus,software,erika.childree@raytheon.com,,,Medium,Done,Jaime_Gamez@raytheon.com,Jaime_Gamez@raytheon.com,Jaime_Gamez@raytheon.com,23/Aug/21 4:22 PM,14/Dec/21 8:05 PM,22/Feb/22 2:44 PM,06/Oct/21 11:44 AM,Team Maturity (AMS) ,,0,AMS,Optimus,team#APP,,,,,,,"Self-organized teams understand each other's roles and tasks and rely less on one particular person as “owner” of something.  These teams do not wait for managers to assign work, instead the team identifies work that needs to be done, prioritizes tasks that are required, and manages timelines on their own.
The purpose of this feature is to self-organize the AMS and Factory team members as a single agile team.
Hypothesis:  Improve efficiency, transparency and alignment as an agile team.  We will spend less time on project management and more time on solving problems and completing work.
A/C:
* Provide an event timeline (Path to PI2)
* Develop the team charter
* Define/Design the EPIC Canvas
* Define/Design the initial feature set for alignment and prioritization

* Prepare the team board with Metrics we will use to improve",,Jaime_Gamez@raytheon.com,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,NOPT-461,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,Applications,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,05/Oct/21 3:59 AM,,,ghx-label-8,,,,,,,(E) AMS and Factory Team Formation,Done,,,,,,,,,,,,,[],,,,,,,,,"0

NET - 004 - Remote Sites Circuits Placed,NOPT-4173,314802,,Feature,PI Committed,NOPT,NTD - Optimus,software,erika.childree@raytheon.com,,,Highest,,Katelyn.C.DEon@raytheon.com,Lauren.Reckert@rtx.com,Lauren.Reckert@rtx.com,17/Aug/21 9:20 PM,08/Feb/22 11:16 AM,22/Feb/22 2:44 PM,,,,0,004,Burndown,CapEdge,ControlTower,Network,Optimus,Team#NET,WAN/MAN,,"Placing orders through Tangoe. Remote sites circuit orders include avpn and ADI circuits
9/1 - awaiting RFP to start circuit orders
9/15 - missing demarc and local contact information for orders
10/25 - still waiting for contracts to be completed
11/10: awaiting for Carrier diversity pricing so that contracts can be completed, BUs will also need to review to validate need for diversity pricing
11/23  - Most of the diversity pricing has been received from ATT. BUs are reviewing sites list to determine which sites need diversity and which constructions costs they are in agreement on.

12/1 - Cost analysis is being redone for single circuits. Pricing will need to be requested from ATT before cost analysis can be provided to the BUs, pending direction from leadership pertaining who is responsible for selecting circuit choices at each site
12/8 - RIS orders were submitted yesterday and RMD orders will be submitted today. Pending PW sites
12/9 - technical pause pending pricing from ATT
1/12/22 - RIS and RMD have been submitted to ATT. PW being finalized to submit
1/14/22- Frank is still working with PW to get their confirmation to order the rest of the remote site circuits.

1/21/22 - PWA/C orders submitted to ATT, with the exception of Puerto Rico, which will be moved to phase 2 due to ATT no bid. We are waiting for contracts for sites 0250 and 8022 for special construction costs. Will close out  this story once we have order numbers from the vendor for all sites.",,,,,,,,,,,,,,,NOPT-7625,,,,,,,,,,,,,NOPT-2073,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,NOPT-2073,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,Network,28/Feb/22 5:00 AM,,,,,,,,,,,,35%,,,,,,,,,,,,,28/Feb/22 5:00 AM,,,,,,,,,,Net - 004 - Track Orders,To Do,,,,,,,,,,,,,[],,,,,,,,,"0
